import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
---

<Layout title="Home Page">
	<main class="content bg-primary-700 txt-dark">
		<div class="newspaper txt-normal">
			<div class="DropCap disclaimer nobreak txt-accent">Note: This site is a work in process and incomplete. If
				you are interested and would like to know more about it, please contact me at <a
					href="mailto:rbishop4561@outlook.com">rbishop4561@outlook.com</a>.</div>
			<div class="intro DropCap nobreak">Welcome to <span class="highlight">Robust Engineering</span> an online
				learning site intending to provide training for those working in product development and would like to
				improve product and/or process robustness. Product robustness here means the product will provide <span
					class="highlight">the intended functions, in stated conditions, for the specified time, in the
					presence of noise</span>.</div>
			<div class="intro nobreak">Some assumptions are made about the experience level of the organization and
				individuals doing the various engineering activities. Links to background information to help close gaps
				are provided below.</div>
			<div class="accent nobreak">Prerequisites:</div>
			<div class="intro DropCap nobreak">A basic understanding of <span class="highlight">statistics</span> is
				essential - a good summary can be found <a rel="noopener" target="_blank"
					href="https://www.w3schools.com/statistics/index.php">here</a></div>
			<div class="intro DropCap nobreak">Since there is likely significant variation in educational background and
				experience, some facility with a few engineering skills will be helpful. Links to prerequisite
				information are provided below for those needing to catch up.</div>
			<div class="accent nobreak">Assumptions and background:</div>
			<div class="highlight nobreak">S-M-A-R-T Requirements</div>
			<div class="indent nobreak">
				<div><span class="highlight">S</span>pecific - and clearly stated</div>
				<div><span class="highlight">M</span>easurable - including units of measure</div>
				<div><span class="highlight">A</span>chievable - otherwise it's a waste of effort</div>
				<div><span class="highlight">R</span>elevany - must reflect what customers want</div>
				<div><span class="highlight">T</span>ime Bound - achievable within project timeframe</div>
			</div>
			<div class="highlight nobreak">Laws of the "famous dead guys"</div>
			<div class="indent nobreak">Newtons 3 laws are important - don't try to break them</div>
			<div class="indent nobreak">Other scientific laws and principles are also to be remembered</div>
			<div class="highlight nobreak">The Scientific Method</div>
			<div class="indent nobreak accent">Hypothosize -&gt; Test -&gt; Validate (or not) -&gt; Repeat</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
